      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s generally dangerous implement functions in headers unless they\u0027re static, especially when they involve float math.  It\u0027s setting things up for silent ODR violations if different copies of these functions are compiled differently, e.g. via SkOpts.\n\n(Even just #including \u003ccmath\u003e can break things when it\u0027s MSVC\u0027s cmath.)",
